Illinois Tool Works Inc Issues FY 2012 Guidance In Line With Analysts' Estimates; Issues Q1 2012 EPS Guidance Below Analysts' Estimates; Comments On Q1 2012 Revenue Guidance
Tuesday, 31 Jan 2012 08:00am EST
Illinois Tool Works Inc announced that for fiscal 2012, it expects diluted income per share from continuing operations to be in a range of $4.02 to $4.26 and assumes a total revenue growth range of 5.0% to 8.0%. For first quarter of 2012, the Company is forecasting diluted income per share from continuing operations to be in a range of $0.89 to $0.97 and assumes a total revenue growth range of 6.0% to 9.0%. The Company reported revenue of $17.787 billion in fiscal 2011. According to I/B/E/S Estimates, analysts were expecting the Company to report EPS of $0.98 on revenues of $4.56 billion for the first quarter of 2012; and EPS of $4.14 on revenues of $18.994 billion for fiscal 2012.Â 
